<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">338. Tilton, John Kent. A History of Color as Used in Textiles. New York:Frank Caso, 1956. Scalamander Silks, Brochure 9. 24 pp. B/W illus. </p><p class="annot">In addition to a brief historical survey of the general dye palette andchanging fashions for textiles, Tilton provides background information on historic associations for each color, color sources for western textiles, and a section on color harmony is included. Although this little book lacks documentation, it provides an pleasant introduction for the student of textiles or interior design. </p></div>
